flowRoot.flowPara: It's all well and good to say, "these Meebles do what I tell them to," but how do the little critters tell you from Alice, Quincy, or Steve? Things are no good if anyone can impersonate anyone!

Authentication is a tricky subject, but the Meebleverse tackles it with "magic wands." A wand is like a remote control, and if you tune the Meebles to listen to one of your wands (and you're the only person with a copy of that wand), then they will only listen to you.

text.tspan: In order to give Meebles to anyone else, I have to be able to

can I tune them to a wand I don't have?
It's not as hard as it sounds. Each wand has an ID number printed on the side of it.

flowRoot.flowPara: What happens if you lose your wand?

If someone else gets a copy of it, they can control all your Meebles - and the first thing a nefarious thief would do, is retune them all to a wand that only thetheif owns. Now you can't control those Meebles, and the theif can.

If you lose your wand, and don't have any backup copies, it's gone forever. There's no locksmith that could get it back - otherwise locksmiths would just steal everybody's Meebles. And since nobody can control the Meebles, no one owns them.
